FONT INFORMATION

The Pomorsky Unicode font is an idealized reproduction of the decorative calligraphic style of book and chapter titles, which was most likely developed in the 1700's by the scribes of the Vyg Hermitage (Vygovskaya Pustyn').

The following files are distributed in this package:
	* PomorskyUnicode.otf : OpenType-CFF font (PostScript outlines) with OpenType features; the internal font name is Pomorsky Unicode
	* PomorskyUnicode.woff : Web Open Font Format font (TrueType outlines) with OpenType features; the internal font name is Pomorsky Unicode
				  This font is intended for embedding into webpages
	* PomorskyUnicode.ttf : TrueType font (TrueType outlines) with OpenType and SIL Graphite features;
				   The internal font name is Pomorsky Unicode TT
	The difference in internal font names allows you to have both the OpenType and TrueType versions installed simultaneously

	* PomorskyUnicode.pdf : The PDF documents demonstrates some features of the font, and lists the available features


